  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">217284_WFP Mt Darwin FFA Zimbabwe</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-ZW&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: &apos;Gill Sans MT&apos;,sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;World Vision will partner with World Food Program to support recovery of the community through a Food Assistance for Assets (FFA) program which is aimed to build resilience of communities, improving their livelihoods situation and enabling the communities to be better prepared to respond to any impending shocks and hazards in wards Kaitano (1), Chigango (33), Pachanza(11). The FFA activities will be layered in three phases that will include the first current cycle focusing on creation of water sources for humans and livestock through borehole drilling and mechanization, establishment of nutrition gardens, construction of livestock water troughs. The second phase will involve construction of a dip tank, orchards and beneficiary trainings while &lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;the final phase will include establishment of woodlots and promoting small livestock production and maintenance of established, conservation activities , assets and strengthening producer groups and VS&amp;amp;L groups. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &apos;Gill Sans MT&apos;, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;&quot;&gt;All activities will be implemented under WFP and WVZ Covid-19 guidelines from 01 May 2021 to 31 December 2021supporting 1316 households in 3 wards. Conditional food transfers amounting to 503mt will be distributed to 1316 participating households in order to address immediate dietary needs.&lt;/span&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
